# 🔐 Environment Configuration Template
# Copy to .env.local and fill in your actual values
# IMPORTANT: Never commit .env file to git!

# Spring Boot Configuration
SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE=prod
SPRING_JPA_HIBERNATE_DDL_AUTO=update
SPRING_JPA_SHOW_SQL=false

# Database Configuration
# For Render PostgreSQL: postgresql://user:password@db.instance.render.com:5432/zenko_db
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/zenko_db

# Java Runtime Options
JAVA_TOOL_OPTIONS=-Xmx512m

# Google OAuth Configuration
# Get from: https://console.cloud.google.com
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id_here.apps.googleusercontent.com
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_google_client_secret_here
GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=https://zenko-backend.onrender.com/login/oauth2/code/google

# OpenRouter API Configuration
# Get free key from: https://openrouter.ai/keys
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Firebase Configuration (Optional)
# Download from Firebase Console → Project Settings
FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=zenko-habit-tracker
FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY=your_firebase_private_key_here
FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL=firebase-adminsdk-xxx@zenko-habit-tracker.iam.gserviceaccount.com
FIREBASE_DATABASE_URL=https://zenko-habit-tracker.firebaseio.com

# Frontend Configuration
REACT_APP_API_URL=https://zenko-backend.onrender.com
REACT_APP_ENV=production

# CORS Configuration
CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://zenko-ai-habit-tracker.vercel.app,https://zenko.tk,http://localhost:3000

# Logging Configuration
LOGGING_LEVEL_ROOT=INFO
LOGGING_LEVEL_COM_ZENKO=DEBUG
   - Check logs: Should see "OpenRouterService Configuration" with `isConfigured(): true`
   - The AI Coach section will show "AI Configured: true"
   - Send a chat message - you should get a real AI response

### Demo Mode

If `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` is not set, the app automatically runs in **demo mode** with pre-canned AI responses. This is useful for development and testing without incurring API costs.

### Security Notes

- ✅ **DO**: Use environment variables
- ❌ **DON'T**: Hardcode keys in source code
- ❌ **DON'T**: Commit keys to git repositories
- ❌ **DON'T**: Share keys in public repositories
- 🔄 **DO**: Rotate keys periodically
- 📝 **DO**: Use different keys for dev/staging/production

### Troubleshooting

**Issue**: AI features not working, "Demo Mode" shown
**Fix**: Ensure `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` is set and the application has been restarted.

**Issue**: "401 Unauthorized" or "Invalid API Key"
**Fix**: Check your API key is correct at https://openrouter.ai/keys

**Issue**: "429 Too Many Requests"
**Fix**: Rate limit reached. The app limits AI endpoints to 20 requests/min. Wait a minute and try again.

**Issue**: Model not found error
**Fix**: The model ID may be incorrect or not available. Check available models at https://openrouter.ai/models

**Issue**: No module named 'jackson' errors
**Fix**: Ensure you have Jackson dependency (already included via spring-boot-starter-web)
